48:28.780 --> 48:32.241
Well, looks like I'm going to Baghdad.

48:32.743 --> 48:35.828
- Two seconds. It was a pleasure.
- Yeah.

48:36.246 --> 48:38.789
- Nice to meet you.
- Good luck to you both.

48:38.832 --> 48:41.250
- Talk to you soon.
- All right.

48:41.335 --> 48:44.003
- I'll talk to you.
- Okay, call me.

48:44.046 --> 48:46.505
- Call me soon.
- Thanks, again.

48:46.548 --> 48:48.049
Bye.

48:57.643 --> 48:59.310
What are you thinking about, right now?

49:00.771 --> 49:01.854
It's funny.

49:01.939 --> 49:03.940
- I was at the Met yesterday.
- Again?

49:04.024 --> 49:06.859
I go every week,
and I noticed a painting,

49:06.902 --> 49:10.029
a watercolor by Bonnard
I've passed every time.

49:10.072 --> 49:16.327
This time I looked at it, and I was
just riveted. It was so beautiful.

49:18.664 --> 49:20.790
I was just wondering
why I never saw it before.

49:22.584 --> 49:27.254
Sometimes we don't see things
until we're ready to see them

49:27.381 --> 49:30.466
in a certain way. You know?

49:32.010 --> 49:33.886
Very true.

49:37.349 --> 49:38.849
Yeah.

49:41.019 --> 49:43.145
What's going on with Ruth and Ethan?

49:45.899 --> 49:50.069
Ethan married a Catholic girl,
and that did not go over well.

49:50.404 --> 49:54.198
- That's why they're fighting?
- Not fighting. They're not talking.

49:54.616 --> 49:58.411
- Two years now. No comunicado.
- Are you serious?

49:58.495 --> 50:02.790
- Totally. It's...
- What? Weren't they close, then?

50:02.958 --> 50:05.960
As close as Ruth and Jake.

50:08.463 --> 50:11.090
- That explains a lot.
- Yeah.

50:11.133 --> 50:13.884
You see why tonight was not just a date.

50:21.476 --> 50:25.104
